1661
01:03:40,310 --> 01:03:42,070
is rotational symmetry.

1662
01:03:44,710 --> 01:03:45,990
A atom,

1663
01:03:45,990 --> 01:03:48,070
in particular a hydrogen atom,

1664
01:03:48,190 --> 01:03:50,610
a hydrogen atom is an electron moving

1665
01:03:50,610 --> 01:03:52,150
in a central force field.

1666
01:03:53,070 --> 01:03:56,330
The equations of a hydrogen atom are rotationally symmetric,

1667
01:03:56,330 --> 01:03:58,470
and that's because the potential energy,

1668
01:03:58,670 --> 01:03:59,830
the Coulomb potential,

1669
01:03:59,970 --> 01:04:01,210
is rotationally symmetric.

1670
01:04:01,470 --> 01:04:02,350
It's a central force.

1671
01:04:03,170 --> 01:04:05,870
And so hydrogen atoms,

1672
01:04:06,050 --> 01:04:08,510
and basically all systems in nature really,

1673
01:04:08,730 --> 01:04:10,690
but hydrogen atoms in particular,

1674
01:04:10,810 --> 01:04:12,850
enjoy rotational symmetry.

1675
01:04:13,450 --> 01:04:14,650
If you rotate...

1676
01:04:14,650 --> 01:04:17,310
All it means is that if you rotate your coordinates,

1677
01:04:18,250 --> 01:04:21,770
the description of the hydrogen atom doesn't change.

1678
01:04:22,350 --> 01:04:24,040
Or another way to say it

1679
01:04:24,040 --> 01:04:25,730
is if you rotate the hydrogen atom,

1680
01:04:25,730 --> 01:04:27,010
it's still a hydrogen atom.

1681
01:04:28,790 --> 01:04:31,070
It may or may not be the same state,

1682
01:04:31,190 --> 01:04:32,430
but it's still a hydrogen atom

1683
01:04:32,430 --> 01:04:34,430
described by the same set of equations.

1684
01:04:37,110 --> 01:04:39,190
So the notion of a symmetry

1685
01:04:39,730 --> 01:04:41,770
is central in quantum mechanics.

1686
01:04:42,070 --> 01:04:44,150
It is also in classical mechanics,

1687
01:04:44,410 --> 01:04:45,940
but it comes up and

1688
01:04:45,940 --> 01:04:47,470
really hits you over the head

1689
01:04:47,470 --> 01:04:48,410
in quantum mechanics.

1690
01:04:50,150 --> 01:04:51,570
And we need to explore,

1691
01:04:53,430 --> 01:04:55,490
largely for the purposes of understanding

1692
01:04:55,730 --> 01:04:56,610
rotational symmetry,

1693
01:04:56,870 --> 01:04:58,850
we need to understand the concept of a symmetry.

